## ✅ Testing Checklist

### Before Committing
```markdown
- [ ] All tests pass locally
- [ ] Coverage thresholds met
- [ ] No skipped tests without justification
- [ ] No console.log in tests
- [ ] Test names clearly describe behavior
- [ ] Mocks are properly cleaned up
- [ ] No hardcoded test data
- [ ] Tests run in isolation
```

### Test Quality Review
```markdown
- [ ] Tests follow AAA pattern (Arrange, Act, Assert)
- [ ] One assertion per test (when possible)
- [ ] Edge cases covered
- [ ] Error scenarios tested
- [ ] Async operations properly handled
- [ ] No implementation details tested
- [ ] Tests document behavior
- [ ] Performance benchmarks included (where relevant)
```

### Error Handling Test Checklist (CRITICAL)
```markdown
**For HTTP Interceptors:**
- [ ] Error object structure verified (userMessage, recoverable properties exist)
- [ ] Error type is correct (HttpErrorResponse with custom properties)
- [ ] Original error properties preserved (status, statusText, url)
- [ ] Network errors (status 0) handled correctly
- [ ] Error can be extracted downstream in catch blocks
- [ ] Error logging includes correct message extraction

**For Error Services:**
- [ ] HttpErrorResponse with userMessage handled
- [ ] HttpErrorResponse with nested error.error handled
- [ ] HttpErrorResponse with nested error.message handled
- [ ] Plain Error instances handled
- [ ] String errors handled
- [ ] Network errors (status 0) marked as recoverable
- [ ] Unknown error types handled gracefully (fallback message)
- [ ] Error extraction logic tested for all paths

**For Components:**
- [ ] Error extraction in catch blocks tested
- [ ] userMessage extracted correctly
- [ ] Nested error.error extracted correctly
- [ ] Plain Error.message extracted correctly
- [ ] String errors handled
- [ ] Error logging includes extracted message (not function stringification)
- [ ] Error service integration tested

**For Logging Interceptors:**
- [ ] Error message extraction from userMessage
- [ ] Error message extraction from nested error.error
- [ ] Error message extraction from nested error.message
- [ ] Error message extraction from Error.message
- [ ] Correlation ID extraction from error headers
- [ ] All error types logged correctly

**For Integration Tests:**
- [ ] Full error flow: HTTP → Interceptor → Service → Component
- [ ] Error structure preserved through chain
- [ ] Error messages remain user-friendly
- [ ] Error extraction works at each layer
- [ ] Error logging occurs at appropriate points
- [ ] Error state management verified
```

## 🚨 Anti-Patterns to Avoid

```typescript
// ❌ BAD: Testing implementation details
it('should call internal method', () => {
  const spy = vi.spyOn(service, '_internalMethod');
  service.publicMethod();
  expect(spy).toHaveBeenCalled(); // Brittle!
});

// ❌ BAD: Multiple assertions without context
it('should work', () => {
  expect(result.a).toBe(1);
  expect(result.b).toBe(2);
  expect(result.c).toBe(3); // Which one failed?
});

// ❌ BAD: Shared mutable state
let sharedUser;
beforeEach(() => {
  sharedUser = { name: 'Test' }; // Can cause test pollution
});

// ❌ BAD: Not testing error object structure
it('should handle errors', (done) => {
  httpClient.get('/api/test').subscribe({
    error: (error) => {
      expect(error).toBeDefined(); // Too vague!
      done();
    },
  });
});

// ❌ BAD: Not testing error extraction in catch blocks
it('should catch errors', async () => {
  try {
    await service.doSomething();
  } catch (error) {
    expect(error).toBeDefined(); // Doesn't verify extraction works!
  }
});

// ✅ GOOD: Test behavior, not implementation
it('should return formatted user name', () => {
  const result = service.getFormattedName({ first: 'John', last: 'Doe' });
  expect(result).toBe('John Doe');
});

// ✅ GOOD: Clear test descriptions
describe('when user is authenticated', () => {
  it('should allow access to protected resources', () => {
    // Test code
  });
});

// ✅ GOOD: Isolated test data
it('should create user', () => {
  const userData = UserFactory.create(); // Fresh data each test
  // Test code
});

// ✅ GOOD: Verify error object structure
it('should create error with userMessage and recoverable properties', (done) => {
  httpClient.get('/api/test').subscribe({
    error: (error) => {
      expect(error.userMessage).toBeDefined();
      expect(typeof error.userMessage).toBe('string');
      expect(error.recoverable).toBeDefined();
      expect(typeof error.recoverable).toBe('boolean');
      done();
    },
  });
});

// ✅ GOOD: Test error extraction pattern used in components
it('should allow error message extraction in catch blocks', async () => {
  let extractedMessage = '';
  try {
    await httpClient.get('/api/test').toPromise();
  } catch (error) {
    if (error && typeof error === 'object') {
      const err = error as { userMessage?: string; message?: string };
      extractedMessage = err.userMessage || err.message || 'Unknown error';
    }
  }
  expect(extractedMessage).toBeTruthy();
});
```

## 📈 Testing Metrics

- **Test Execution Time**: < 5 minutes for unit tests
- **E2E Execution Time**: < 15 minutes for critical paths
- **Test Flakiness**: < 2% failure rate
- **Coverage Trend**: Increasing or stable, never decreasing
- **Mutation Score**: > 80% for critical modules
- **Test-to-Code Ratio**: ~1.5:1 for business logic

